      "message": "food for thought -- just thinking out loud so that either you can correct me and/or my thoughts can help speed up our code in the future.\n\nyou are loading 2 entities here *sequentially*, which means two roundtrips to datastore + delays. In general, prefer to read both in a single datastore.Get.\n\nDuring migration, we\u0027ll almost always need to load 3 kinds of entities here:\n1. Run itself. [Always needed.]\n2. Either RunFinished or RunVerified entity from CQD\n[possibly not exists, possibly not needed to be loaded in some cases]\n3. RunCLs.\n[I think these are always needed]\n\n(1) and (2) can be loaded at the same time, since their IDs are known in advance.\n(3) can only be loaded once you get Run entity.\nThus, ideal is \n  first: datastore.Get(\u0026Run, \u0026RUnFInished, \u0026RunVerified)\n  second: datastore.Get([\u0026RunCL for cl in run.cls])\n\nUnfortunately, loading 2+ entities via datastore.Get() is somewhat annoying wrt dealing with errors.\nAlso, once CQDaemon is deleted we won\u0027t need (2).\n\nSo, perhaps it\u0027s OK to write simpler code with 3 sequential RPCs to datastore today in (1) (2) (3) order, s.t. it\u0027s easy to remove step (2) once CQDaemon is dead.",
